LAGOS – Following the warm reception he received during his consultative visit to Kaduna State today, APC National leader and Presidential candidate in the forthcoming 2023 presidential election, Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu has expressed profound gratitude to the Governor of Kaduna State, Nasir Ahmad El-Rufai and all Kaduna State APC members. According to him, he was deeply touched by the manner of hospitality to which he was treated. -Advertisement- “My sincere gratitude to my brother, Governor Nasir Ahmad el-Rufai and all Kaduna State APC members for their welcoming reception during my visit to their state today. I was indeed touched by their hospitality and heartfelt support. I stand with you.” See tweet below; My sincere gratitude to my brother, Governor Nasir Ahmad el-Rufai and all Kaduna State APC members for their welcoming reception during my visit to their state today.I was indeed touched by their hospitality and heartfelt support.I stand with you. #BAT2023 pic.twitter.com/GEZppwV8Zp